mean_round <- function(numbers,sig_digits=2){
 return(round(mean(as.numeric(numbers),na.rm=TRUE),sig_digits))
}

Alzheimer’s Data

alz_raw <- read.csv("alzheimers.csv") %>% janitor::clean_names()
alz_raw <- alz_raw %>% filter(year == "2021") 
alz_raw <- alz_raw %>% select(state, rate)

Physical Inactivity Data

inactive_raw <- read.csv("inactivity.csv") %>% janitor::clean_names()
inactive_raw <- inactive_raw %>% filter(class == "Physical Activity") %>% filter(question == "Percent of adults who engage in no leisure-time physical activity †")

inactive_raw <- inactive_raw %>% select(location_abbr, data_value)

inactive_raw <- inactive_raw %>% filter(location_abbr != "DC" & location_abbr != "PR", 
                                     location_abbr != "US", location_abbr != "VI",
                                     location_abbr != "GU")
inactive_raw <- inactive_raw %>% rename(state = location_abbr) %>% rename(percent_inactive = data_value)

inactive_raw$percent_inactive <- sub("~", "", inactive_raw$percent_inactive)
inactive_raw$percent_inactive <- as.numeric(as.character(inactive_raw$percent_inactive))
inactive_raw$active <- (100 - inactive_raw$percent_inactive)
inactive_raw <- inactive_raw %>% select(state, active)

Obesity Data

obesity_raw <- read.csv("obesity.csv") %>% janitor::clean_names()

obesity_raw <- obesity_raw %>% select(location_abbr, data_value) %>% group_by(location_abbr) %>% summarize(obesity = mean_round(data_value))

obesity_raw <- obesity_raw %>% filter(location_abbr != "DC" & location_abbr != "PR", 
                                     location_abbr != "US", location_abbr != "VI",
                                     location_abbr != "GU")
obesity_raw <- obesity_raw %>% rename(state = location_abbr) 

obesity_raw$obesity <- sub("NaN", "", obesity_raw$obesity)
obesity_raw$obesity <- as.numeric(as.character(obesity_raw$obesity))

Age Data

age_raw <- read.csv("age.csv") %>% janitor::clean_names()
age_raw <- age_raw %>% slice(25)
age_raw <- age_raw %>% select(ends_with("percent"))
age_raw <- age_raw %>%
  pivot_longer(everything(), 
               names_to = "state", 
               values_to = "percent") %>%
  separate("state", into = c("state", "info"), sep = "(?<=\\D)(?=\\d)")

healthcare <- read.csv("healthcare.csv") %>% janitor::clean_names()
healthcare <- healthcare %>% rename(state = x) 
healthcare <- healthcare %>% rename(money = x_1) 
healthcare <- healthcare %>% filter(state != "District of Columbia")
healthcare$money <- sub("\\$", "", healthcare$money)
healthcare$money <- sub(",", "", healthcare$money)

Combining to one Data Frame

combined_df <- alz_raw %>% full_join(commute_raw, by = "state") %>% full_join(obesity_raw, by = "state") %>%
  full_join(inactive_raw, by = 'state') %>% full_join(age_raw, by = 'state') %>%
  full_join(healthcare, by = 'state')

5. Interaction

combined_df <- combined_df %>% na.omit()
interaction_plot <- lm(rate ~ bike_walk * active, data = combined_df)
summary(interaction_plot)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = rate ~ bike_walk * active, data = combined_df)
## 
## Residuals:

mean_active <- mean(combined_df$active)
sd_active <- sd(combined_df$active)

plot_data_lines <- data.frame(
  bike_walk = rep(seq(min(combined_df$bike_walk), max(combined_df$bike_walk), length = 100), 2),
  active = rep(c(mean_active - sd_active, mean_active + sd_active), each = 100)
)

plot_data_lines$rate_pred <- predict(interaction_plot, newdata = plot_data_lines)


ggplot(data = combined_df, aes(x = bike_walk, y = rate)) +
  geom_line(data = plot_data_lines, aes(x = bike_walk, y = rate_pred, color = as.factor(active)), size = 1) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(x = "% of Citizens who Bike/Walk to Work", y = "Alzheimer's Mortality Rate", 
       title = "Exploring the Influence of Biking/Walking to Work and 
       Physical Activity Levels on Alzheimer's Mortality Rates") +
  scale_color_manual(
    values = c("blue", "red"), 
    name = "Physical Activity Level",
    breaks = c(mean_active - sd_active, mean_active + sd_active),
    labels = c("One SD Below Mean", "One SD Above Mean")
  ) + 
  ylim(10,50) +
  xlim(1,5) +
  theme_bw()
